{
  "id": "algebra-1-ch03-sec06",
  "title": "Chapter Review",
  "chapter": 3,
  "section": 6,
  "book": "algebra-1",
  "epigraph": {
    "text": "Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as \nworking for the Lord, not for human masters.",
    "reference": "Colossians 3:23",
    "quote": "Practice makes perfect.",
    "quoteAuthor": "Attributed to many"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{Practice makes perfect.}{Attributed to many}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This chapter has taken us on a journey through the art of equation solving. \nBeginning with the simplest one-step equations, we built up our skills to \nhandle multi-step equations, equations with variables on both sides, and \nliteral equations with multiple variables. Along the way, we discovered \nthat algebra is fundamentally about balance: whatever we do to one side of \nan equation, we must do to the other."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Let us review the key concepts and practice the techniques we have learned."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts Summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Section-by-Section Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 3.1: One-Step Equations**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Solve equations using a single inverse operation.",
        "Addition undoes subtraction; multiplication undoes division.",
        "Always check your solution."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 3.2: Two-Step Equations**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Undo addition/subtraction first, then multiplication/division.",
        "This reverses the order of operations."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 3.3: Multi-Step Equations**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Combine like terms on each side.",
        "Use the distributive property to remove parentheses.",
        "Clear fractions by multiplying by the LCD.",
        "Clear decimals by multiplying by a power of 10."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 3.4: Equations with Variables on Both Sides**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Gather variable terms on one side, constants on the other.",
        "Be alert for identity equations and contradictions."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Section 3.5: Literal Equations and Formulas**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Treat other variables as if they were numbers.",
        "Factor out the variable you're solving for when it appears in \n multiple terms."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chapter Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**One-Step Equations (Section 3.1)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation and check your solution."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x + 17 = 29$",
        "$y - 8 = -15$",
        "$5m = -45$",
        "$\\dfrac{n}{6} = 12$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $-7x = 63$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $\\dfrac{3}{4}y = 18$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Two-Step Equations (Section 3.2)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$3x + 7 = 22$",
        "$5y - 9 = 31$",
        "$\\dfrac{m}{4} + 6 = 11$",
        "$-2n + 15 = 7$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $\\dfrac{2}{3}x - 8 = 4$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $0.4y + 1.6 = 4$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Multi-Step Equations (Section 3.3)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$4x + 3 + 2x = 27$",
        "$7y - 5 - 2y = 20$",
        "$3(m + 4) = 30$",
        "$2(3n - 5) + 4 = 18$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $5(x + 2) - 3(x - 1) = 17$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $\\dfrac{x}{3} + \\dfrac{x}{4} = 7$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $\\dfrac{2x + 3}{5} = 3$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Equations with Variables on Both Sides (Section 3.4)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$7x + 5 = 4x + 20$",
        "$3y - 8 = 5y + 10$",
        "$4(m + 2) = 2(m + 8)$",
        "$6n - 3 = 2(3n - 1)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Classify each equation as having one solution, no solution, or infinitely \nmany solutions. Solve if possible."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$5x + 3 = 5x + 7$",
        "$2(y + 4) = 2y + 8$",
        "$3m - 5 = 2m + 4$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve: $\\dfrac{x + 2}{3} = \\dfrac{x - 4}{5}$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Literal Equations (Section 3.5)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation for the indicated variable."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$d = rt$ for $r$",
        "$P = 2l + 2w$ for $w$",
        "$A = \\frac{1}{2}bh$ for $h$",
        "$V = \\pi r^2 h$ for $h$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve $y = mx + b$ for $x$."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve $F = \\frac{9}{5}C + 32$ for $C$."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve $S = 2\\pi r^2 + 2\\pi rh$ for $h$."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Mixed Practice"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solve each equation. State if the equation has no solution or infinitely \nmany solutions."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$8x - 5 = 3x + 25$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$4(y + 3) = 2(y - 5)$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$\\dfrac{2m + 1}{3} = \\dfrac{m - 2}{4}$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$0.5x + 0.3 = 0.2x + 0.9$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$6(n - 2) + 4 = 3(2n - 3)$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$\\dfrac{x}{2} - \\dfrac{x}{5} = 3$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$-3(2y + 4) = -6y - 12$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$7m + 2(m - 5) = 9m + 1$"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Word Problems"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The sum of a number and 15 is 42. Find the number."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Three times a number, decreased by 7, equals 23. Find the number."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The length of a rectangle is 4 more than twice its width. If the perimeter \nis 62 cm, find the dimensions."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A taxi charges \\$3.00 plus \\$2.50 per mile. If a ride costs \\$18.00, how \nmany miles was the trip?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Two hikers start from the same point. One hikes north at 3 mph; the other \nhikes south at 4 mph. How long until they are 21 miles apart?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The sum of three consecutive integers is 84. Find the integers."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After a 20\\% discount, a shirt costs \\$36. What was the original price?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A phone plan costs \\$35 per month plus \\$0.15 per minute of calls. If \nthe monthly bill was \\$62, how many minutes of calls were made?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Two cars leave from the same point at the same time. One travels east \nat 50 mph and the other travels west at 60 mph. After how many hours \nwill they be 385 miles apart?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The formula for converting Celsius to Fahrenheit is $F = 1.8C + 32$. \nAt what temperature do Celsius and Fahrenheit have the same numerical \nvalue? (Hint: Set $F = C$ and solve.)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Challenging Problems"
    }
  ]
}